 is a two-way exchange that requires a readiness on the part of the host society to remove barriers that prevent the full social and economic participation of immigrant populations. Extensively researched and thoughtfully provocative, Diaspora by Design is a much-needed work that provides an accurate and dynamic depiction of the lives of Muslim immigrants away from their homelands.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aMuslim diaspora. 0aMuslimsvStatistics. 0aMuslimszCanadavStatistics. 0aMuslimszCanada. 4aCoursebook. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / General.2bisacsh1 aGoodman, Mark , eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRahnema, Saeed, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311049095440uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144268787540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442687875423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442687875.jpg  a978-3-11-049095-4  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK